                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d869">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14703.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister to Mexico</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-29T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 29, 1915—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>596. Answering your 459, March 26, midnight: Your suggestion in regard to neutral
                    zone is cordially approved and has been transmitted to Carranza and Villa with
                    an earnest recommendation that it be agreed upon. Am very much gratified that
                    you have, secured the consent of Garza.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
